Overview:
---------
	Orbots the Game is a heart pounding,  brain boggling,  shoot 'em up,
	extravaganza.  Super smooth 256 color VGA graphics are complemented
	with extraordinary digital sound.  An adrenaline junkies dream!
	You must pilot the astro-chopper to defeat an invasion of half machine,
	half organo mutants from another dimension.  They have plenty of
	surprises for you, and some nasty tricks for you to figure out.  If you
	get through their defenses,  you still must face their mother ship to
	defeat them.
        Good Luck. You'll need it!  <ASP>

Chapter One:
------------
1.1 System Requirements
		The game requires an IBM compatible computer with a 386
	processor or better. A colour VGA video monitor and compatible video
	card.  It is also recommended that you have a MS compatible mouse
	(the game was designed for a mouse, but will also support a
	joystick, or the keyboard).  For sound you require a compatible
	sound card with speakers (see Chapter Two Sound Card Hoop-La for
	more details).  The game has been written to use memory wisely,
	so 640K of conventional memory is all that is required. The full game
	takes up approximately 2.5MB of hard disk drive space. You also
	must have DOS 3.3 or later.

1.2  Installation
		Please run the supplied install program to install the
	game.

	- Just type install at a dos prompt and follow the instructions.
	- The game will ask you to setup sound cards, etc.
	  when the game is started for the first time by typing 'orbots',
	  at a dos prompt.
	- To remove the game, simply delete all files from the Orbots
	  the Game directory.


