1.4 Memory
		To use the game with full rich sound and digital effects,
	the game requires 554K of free conventional memory and a 16-bit
	sound card. 8-bit sound cards will not work as well but are far
	superior to the PC speaker. You can check your memory by using the
	DOS "mem or mem/c" command. See your DOS reference manual for
	details. If you are not using any of the sounds or music, the game
	requires only 350K free conventional memory. To make more memory
	see section 2.5. To reset the game to min. memory see section 2.4.

