4.5  Error Messages
	- Not Enough Memory  - you do not have the required amount of free
	  conventional memory to run all the features.  Correct this problem
	  or turn off the sound effects, music. See sections 2.4 and 2.5.
	- Error Loading  %%  - This is a fatal error.  Stops program. A
	  file is missing from the game directory, or a file is corrupt.
          Download a new copy of the game from Compuserve (GO PIKAPRO).
          Or visit www.pik.com on the Internet.
	- Error Loading Sound System - Fatal error. stops program.
	  Incorrect hardware or missing file in game directory.
	- Error loading driver - selected sound driver is not compatible
	  with hardware or file is missing from game directory.
	- Error init driver - wrong sound driver IRQ,DMA or address
	  information.
	- Error opening sound - missing file in game directory.
	- Mouse driver not detected - You don't have a mouse, your mouse
	  is not MS compatible, or the controller setting is wrong.
	- No joystick detected - You don't have a joystick or it is not
	  connected as joystick 0.
	- Unknown error! - contact Sunshower Systems and report any numbers
	  that appear with the error message.

